We recommended the Local Chief Executive to direct the Municipal Accountant and the General Services Officer to do the following:

a) Execute periodic reconciliation of property cards to ensure that all discrepancies are immediately investigated, cleared and reconciled with the books of accounts;

b) Make needed journal entries to adjust the duly investigated reconciling items on order to reflect the accurate account balances;

