We recommended that the Municipal Mayor should:
a) Require the completion of the physical inventory report;
b) Instruct the General Services Officer to officially request the GSIS to conduct evaluation of properties for the consideration in the insurance plan;
c) Direct the General Services Officer to coordinate with the Municipal Budget Officer in the estimation of premium that may be incurred for the insurance plan; and
d) Advise the Municipal Budget Officer to appropriate the necessary amount to cover for the payment of premium for the insurance of the properties in annual budget. We further recommended strict compliance with R.A. No. 656.

